whole
Pacific
slope.
It
was
not
the
father,
however,
who
first
discovered
that
the
child
had
developed
into
the
woman.
It
seldom
is
in
such
cases.
That
mysterious
change
is
too
subtle
and
too
gradual
to
be
measured
by
dates.
Least
of
